#: ../../helpsupport.rst:91
msgid ""
"Installing |trueos| is usually very simple. However, sometimes problems "
"occur. This section examines solutions to the most common installation "
"problems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../helpsupport.rst:95
msgid ""
"The |trueos| installer creates a log which keeps a record of all the "
"completed steps, as well as any errors. When an installation error occurs, "
"the |trueos| installer asks to generate an error report. If :guilabel:`Yes` "
"is chosen, a pop-up message asks to save the error log to a USB stick. Type "
":kbd:`y` and insert a FAT formatted USB thumb drive to copy the log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../helpsupport.rst:121
msgid ""
"If the computer freezes while probing hardware and unplugging extra devices "
"does not fix the problem, it is possible that the installation media is "
"corrupt. If the :ref:`Data Integrity check` on the downloaded file is "
"correct, try burning the file again at a lower speed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../helpsupport.rst:136
msgid ""
"A common cause for problems is the *LBA* (Logical Block Addressing) setting "
"in the BIOS. If the PC is not booting before or after installation, check "
"the BIOS and turn *LBA* off (do not leave it on automatic)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../helpsupport.rst:141
msgid ""
"If the SATA settings in the BIOS are set to *compatibility* mode, try "
"changing this setting to *AHCI*. If the system hangs with a BTX error, try "
"turning off *AHCI* in the BIOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../helpsupport.rst:145
msgid ""
"If the USB keyboard is non-functional, check if there is an option in the "
"BIOS for *legacy support* in relation to the keyboard, USB, or both. "
"Enabling this feature in the BIOS may solve this issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../helpsupport.rst:156
msgid ""
"If none of the above has fixed the problem, the :ref:`TrueOS Community` is a"
" valuable resource to assist in tracking down and solving the issue."
msgstr ""

